  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "These results are in line with a number of articles that have shown, outside of silicon sampling tasks, that LLMs have significant biases.",
    "By this, their authors mean that the responses of the models are skewed towards a certain country, one or a few social groups, or a given political ideology.",
    "In a large comparative study, Atari et al. (2023) found a near-perfect correlation between a WEIRDness scale for each country and the distance between the LLM prediction and the actual human response.",
    "Probing ChatGPT, Motoki et al. (2024) found evidence of a political bias favoring liberal views (see also Rutinowski et al., 2024; Hartmann et al., 2023; Rozado, 2024).",
    "Others confirmed this insight (Cao et al., 2023), while Johnson et al. (2022) wittily noted that GPT-3 \"has an American accent.\""
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In a large comparative study, Atari et al. (2023) found a near-perfect correlation between a WEIRDness scale for each country and the distance between the LLM prediction and the actual human response.",
    "Probing ChatGPT, Motoki et al. (2024) found evidence of a political bias favoring liberal views (see also Rutinowski et al., 2024; Hartmann et al., 2023; Rozado, 2024).",
    "Others confirmed this insight (Cao et al., 2023), while Johnson et al. (2022) wittily noted that GPT-3 \"has an American accent.\""
  ]
